In this proclamation issued by President Donald Trump on April 22, 2020, he states that the COVID-19 pandemic has significantly impacted the livelihoods of Americans, leading to high levels of unemployment. He expresses concern about the impact of foreign workers on the labor market, especially during a time of high domestic unemployment. The proclamation suspends and limits the entry of certain aliens as immigrants for the next 60 days, with exceptions for lawful permanent residents, healthcare professionals, and others deemed essential. The proclamation also calls for a review of nonimmigrant programs to prioritize the hiring and employment of American workers. It states that the policy aims to protect the interests of the United States and can be continued or modified as necessary.